Marie Leroy is Iola and Harry’s mother, Eugene Leroy’s wife, and a former slave. As a mulatta herself, Marie is conflicted over her husband’s refusal to inform their children of their black heritage. The merciful and compassionate Marie cares for her slave master during his illness and his spiritual decline. Overtly maternal, Marie is dedicated to her children. She is also industrious and employs her skills in the domestic arts to sustain herself financially.